Dacier suggests that he wrote a tragedy with this title, to which notion the following lines give some probability. Horace says that Furius, like some rude artists, had made a figure of Rhenus with a head of clay, refer-ring to the statues by which the different river gods were represented, and to some description this poet had given of the sources of the Rhine, probably in the above poem on the Gallie war.
